{
  "texts": [
    "We show that it is a closed subspace.",
    "To that end, let T i ∈ P d be a sequence converging to T ∈ C(K) with respect to the norm ∥•∥ C(K).",
    "Note that since each T i is actually a functional on all of Lip b × [Lip] d, the map T has a natural extension to Lip b × [Lip] d given, for example, byT (f, π) = lim i T i (f, π).Since pointwise limits of linear functionals are linear, it follows that T is multilinear.",
    "Since T lies in the space C(K), it is jointly continuous.",
    "It remains to show that T is local."
  ]
}